                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_bappa" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>bappa</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>bappu</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>хлеб</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> („детское“ слово)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (a “child” word)</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>bread</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> („детское“ слово)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (a “child” word)</note></sense><etym xml:lang="ru">Распространенное на кавказской почве „детское“ слово: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>baba</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/> <w>babul</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>bepig</w></mentioned> (для -%iig%i || -%iа%i ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>žižig</w></mentioned> || ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ʒīʒa"/> ‘мясо’ на „детском“ языке), <mentioned xml:lang="kap"><lang/> <w>baba</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/> <w>bappu</w></mentioned> и др. Ср. также <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>pappa</w> <gloss><q>детская каша</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It is a widespread child word of Caucasian origin: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>baba</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/> <w>babul</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>bepig</w></mentioned> (for -%iig%i || -%iа%i cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>žižig</w></mentioned> || Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ʒīʒa"/> ‘meat’ in “child” language), <mentioned xml:lang="kap"><lang/> <w>baba</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/> <w>bappu</w></mentioned> etc. Cf. also <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>pappa</w> <gloss><q>child porridge</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>